OL,3,CGovernment urged to improve response
OL,4,Cto 'world-beatingly high' energy bills
OL,6,FThe Government should improve its
OL,7,Fresponse to future energy price spikes
OL,8,Fas Britons face "world-beatingly high"
OL,9,Fbills, Parliament's spending watchdog
OL,10,Fsaid.
OL,12,FElectricity bills in 2023 were the
OL,13,Fhighest among comparable countries,
OL,14,Fwith consumers owing #3.7 billion for
OL,15,Fgas and electricity in 2024, more than
OL,16,Fdouble the amount in 2021, the Public
OL,17,FAccounts Committee's report said.
