OL,3,CGovernment urged to improve response
OL,4,Cto 'world-beatingly high' energy bills
OL,6,FThe PAC urged the Department for
OL,7,FEnergy Security and Net Zero (DESNZ)
OL,8,Fto improve support for households
OL,9,Fvulnerable to fuel poverty and create
OL,10,Fa clear plan and timeline for policy
OL,11,Fdecisions to make bills cheaper.
OL,13,FChairman of the committee Sir Geoffrey
OL,14,FClifton-Brown said: "Sharp moves in
OL,15,Fenergy prices in the future must find
OL,16,FGovernment fully prepared to issue
OL,17,Ftargeted and effective support, with
OL,18,Fthose most in need the focus of that
OL,19,Fsupport.
OL,26,@vD@UOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
