OL,3,CGovernment urged to improve response
OL,4,Cto 'world-beatingly high' energy bills
OL,6,FThe PAC said the DESNZ has been slow
OL,7,Fto learn from past energy price spikes
OL,8,Fand cannot yet target support
OL,9,Feffectively, as some people who did
OL,10,Fnot need help still received aid from
OL,11,Fthe #44 billion energy bill support
OL,12,Fschemes.
OL,14,FIt urged the DESNZ to develop more
OL,15,Ffinancial support for consumers in
OL,16,Ftime for next winter, saying the
OL,17,Fdepartment and energy regulator Ofgem
OL,18,F"are not doing enough" to ensure
OL,19,Fpeople falling into debt with their
OL,20,Fenergy bills receive proper advice and
OL,21,Fsupport.
